==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spilikin
<hw>Spil"i*kin</hw> <pr>(sp⟦icr⟧l"⟦icr⟧*k⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OD. <ets>spelleken</ets> a small pin. See <er>Spill</er> a
splinter.]</ety> <def>One of a number of small pieces or pegs of wood,
ivory, bone, or other material, for playing a game, or for counting the
score in a game, as in cribbage. In the plural
(<plw><it>spilikins</it></plw>), a game played with such pieces;
pushpin.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>spillikin</asp>,
<asp>spilliken</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spill</ent>⟦br⟧
